Q-1. Write an SQL query to fetch “FIRST_NAME” from  Employee table using the alias name as  
<EMPLOYEE_NAME>. 
Ans. 

select first_name as EMPLOYEE_NAME from emp;

+---------------+
| EMPLOYEE_NAME |
+---------------+
| Monika        |
| Niharika      |
| Vishal        |
| Amitabh       |
| Vivek         |
| Vipul         |
| Anuj          |
| Priya         |
+---------------+
=============================================================================================================================================================================


Q-2. Write an SQL query to fetch “FIRST_NAME” from  EMPLOYEE table in upper case. 
Ans. 

mysql> select upper(first_name) as EMPLOYEE_NAME from emp;

+---------------+
| EMPLOYEE_NAME |
+---------------+
| MONIKA        |
| NIHARIKA      |
| VISHAL        |
| AMITABH       |
| VIVEK         |
| VIPUL         |
| ANUJ          |
| PRIYA         |
