Q-4. Write an SQL query to print the first three characters  of FIRST_NAME from EMPLOYEE table. 
Ans. 

mysql> select substring(first_name,1,3) as Frist_three_char from emp;

+------------------+
| Frist_three_char |
+------------------+
| Mon              |
| Nih              |
| Vis              |
| Ami              |
| Viv              |
| Vip              |
| Anu              |
| Pri              |
+------------------+
=============================================================================================================================================================================

Q-5. Write an SQL query to find the position of the  alphabet (‘a’) in the first name column ‘Amitabh’ from  EMPLOYEE table. 
Ans. 

select first_name,instr(first_name,'a') as Position from emp where first_name='Amitabh';

+------------+----------+
| first_name | Position |
+------------+----------+
| Amitabh    |        1 |
+------------+----------+
=============================================================================================================================================================================

