Q-24. Write an SQL query to print details of the  EMPLOYEEs who are also Managers. 
Ans.  select e.* ,t.emp_title
    -> from emp e
    ->  join title t on t.emp_id = e.emp_id where t.emp_title ="manager";

+--------+------------+-----------+-----------+---------------------+------------+-----------+
| emp_id | first_name | last_name | salary    | joining_date        | department | emp_title |
+--------+------------+-----------+-----------+---------------------+------------+-----------+
|      1 | Monika     | Arora     | 100000.00 | 2014-02-20 09:00:00 | HR         | Manager   |
|      5 | Vivek      | Bhati     | 500000.00 | 2014-06-11 09:00:00 | Admin      | Manager   |
+--------+------------+-----------+-----------+---------------------+------------+-----------+
=============================================================================================================================================================================

Q-25. Write an SQL query to fetch duplicate records having  matching data in some fields of a table. 
Ans. mysql> SELECT First_Name, Last_Name, Department, COUNT(*)
    -> FROM emp
    -> GROUP BY First_Name, Last_Name, Department
    -> HAVING COUNT(*) > 1;
Empty set (0.00 sec)
=============================================================================================================================================================================

Q-26. Write an SQL query to show only odd rows from a  table. 
Ans. 

